The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | PwC to ramp up India team
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      PwC to ramp up India team
          SOUNAK MITRA                              
	Calcutta, Jan. 23: PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) will hire about 1,500-1,800 professionals for its India advisory team over the next two years, PwC global head (advisory services) Juan A. Pujadas said.        
	Based on the business trend in India, we will need to increase the headcount of our advisory team by 50-60 per cent over the next two years, Pujadas told The Telegraph.         
	At present, there are 3,000 professionals in PwCs advisory team in India.         
	Last year, PwC international chairman designate Dennis Nally said the company would increase its India headcount by 3,500 over the next 3-4 years across all verticals, taking the total staff strength to over 10,000.        
	India is a strategic market for the global consultancy firm and will become increasingly important for it and international clients over the next few years, Pujadas said.        
	In India, PwC has three major wings  consultancy, advisory and audit. Advisory contributes over 40 per cent business in India, PwC executive director (business advisory) Sharat Bansal said.         
	According to Pujadas, around 10 per cent of the companys global advisory services staff are based in India. Globally, there are about 30,000 professionals who work for PwCs advisory services.                                                                                                                                       
